  A bunch of bananas proved to be a greater challenge for tennis pro Denis Shapovalov than his opponent at the Australian Open on Monday. As the 18-year-old Canadian was cruising to a straight-set, first-round victory over Greece's Stefanos Tsitsipas, he tried to peel several bananas courtside, failing each time. It looked like a modern vaudeville act. This win is bananas, B-A-N-A-N-A-S!#AusOpen@denis_shapopic.twitter.com/pW3hPnzkmp Finally, the flustered Shapovalov was able to pry one open, and he clenched his fist in victory. "I think I played extremely well today," Shapovalov told news outlets. But your snacking game needs work, kid. H/T For The Win